{"lemma":"خاشِعَةٍ","slug":"خاشِعَةٍ","root":"خ.ش.ع","root_slug":"خ-ش-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ش-ع","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خاشِع","root":"خشع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":14},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n10681"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B4%D9%90%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of خَشَعَ (ḵašaʕa)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"who is humble, looking down and reverently submissive (especially in worship)","examples":[{"text":"الَّذِينَ هُمْ فِي صَلَاتِهِمْ خَاشِعُونَ","english":"those who humble themselves in prayer."},{"text":"وُجُوهٌ يَوْمَئِذٍ خَاشِعَةٌ","english":"On that Day ˹some˺ faces will be downcast."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of خَشَعَ (ḵašaʕa)."},"ipa":["/xaː.ʃiʕ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n10681","headword_ar":"خَاشِعٌ","root":"x$E","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lowly, humble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and still:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so in the voice"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the eyes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 1:)] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaA$iEuwna","text_ar":"خَاشِعُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu$~aEN","text_ar":"خُشَّعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the latter also signifying men"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowering, humbling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abasing, themselves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constraining themselves to be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to become, lowly, humble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be so,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to become so, in voice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the eyes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"casting their eyes towards the ground, and lowering their voices."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Hence, in the Kur"},{"kind":"page_break","n":743},{"kind":"text","text":"[lxviii. 43, and lxx. 44], accord. to different readings,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaA$iEapF A^aboSaAruhumo","text_ar":"خَاشِعَةً اَبْصَارُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaA$iEFA A^aboSaAruhumo","text_ar":"خَاشِعًا اَبْصَارُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having their eyes cast down"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: the accus. case being used as denotative of state. (Zj, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bowing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bending down the head and body."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fearing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  (tropical:)  A camel's foot ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuf~N","text_ar":"خُفٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cleaving to the ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  (tropical:)  A wall"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has cracked, and given notice of its falling, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"then"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become even with the ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  (tropical:)  A herb"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dried up, and falling down upon the ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-  Applied to a place, (S, K,) and, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balodap","text_ar":"بَلْدَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or portion of country], (S,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Overspread with dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuEanobaru","text_ar":"المُعَنْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almugab~aru","text_ar":"المُغَبَّرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and having in it no place of alighting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of abiding:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) and to land ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the wind raises the surface, by reason of its softness, so as to efface its traces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tracks:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or in this case it is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the Kur xli. 39, and means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altered"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutagay~irap","text_ar":"مُتَغَيِّرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[probably a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutagab~irap","text_ar":"مُتَغَبِّرَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overspread with dust"},{"kind":"text","text":"]),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and having its herbage broken in pieces:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, * TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dried up, and containing no herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"containing no green herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depressed, and still:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and, without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a place,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to which one finds not his way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu$~aEN","text_ar":"خُشَّعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","L","Jel","Sgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}